{"questionId":"c01f4a95","correctAnswer":"39","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Substitute the given value","content":"With $j(x)=mx+144$ and $j(12)=18$, plug $x=12$:<br/>$$12m+144=18\\;\\Rightarrow\\;12m=-126\\;\\Rightarrow\\;m=-\\tfrac{21}{2}$$"},{"title":"Solve for the unknown","content":"Now compute $j(10)=-\\tfrac{21}{2}(10)+144=-105+144=39$.<br/>The answer is <strong>39</strong>."}]}